snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve had depression ever since I could start remembering things and having memories.
My emotional pain eventually turned into using pain medicine. Although when I started taking it it was for my physical pain, but then it became for my emotional pain.
I started to cry so hard listening to this... because I relate in just about every aspect. I feel alone even when surrounded by people. I feel invisible in my own house and I just went through my first breakup in September from the man I’ve been with for almost 9 years. And now I’m worse off than I have ever been. I have cried every single day since he left me and him leaving me brought back emotions I haven’t felt since I was single years ago and I don’t even know how to sort these emotions out. I’ve been suicidal since 2007, and up until the breakup I had attempted twice and been in a mental hospital each time and now I’ve attempted six times. And I’m still here, and believe me each time I attempted I should have died. And for some fucked up reason I’m still here. I have never felt like my voice was heard. No one listens to me, my ex was the only person that ever did. This pain.... this fucking pain is relentless and I don’t know which way to turn. I feel stupid every time I pray, but I’m so desperate when I’m crying so hard I can’t breathe I just yell out loud for the lord to help me and I feel so dumb. I feel dumb even writing this comment. It’s just a comment on YouTube and here I am writing something that’ll never be heard.
You’re not alone Demi, an I’m sure you know that, but you truly have no idea. Atleast you have this beautiful voice as an outlet. I’m listening Demi, I’m listening....

snippet.textDisplay: Back in 2009, I paid $20.00, $10. each, for two tickets and took my daughter to see you, Demi. Her very first concert, she was 10 yrs old and we had such a great time. I remember thinking what an amazing voice this young kid on stage had, even then the power in that child's voice stood out above others to me. Seeing this performance today still blows me away. I myself have been sober for 18 years now and it is a battle, but one that can be won! All these years later my struggle is depression mainly. I can be sitting like I am now and be hit out of nowhere with a memory or just deep sadness and at times it is like an ongoing war. But at the end of the day, I win and you will to luv. I still have our tickets to that concert and a pic of you that was made for all of your fans, in a frame still to this day. We are listening, we care, I pray, and you will most definitely WIN this battle you are fighting. YOU ARE SO NOT ALONE LUV!

snippet.textDisplay: I honestly am reading these comments and just thinking to myself like "it's easy to say things and judge from a perspective where you haven't been in another person's situation such as Demi" vs actually being in a place where she's been and experiencing the things that she's has knowing how it feels and where it can take a person. Yes it is quite sad and while some of y'all or most feel like she's rich and privileged and she should be able to get "help" on her own. You really don't know what goes on behind close doors of this music industry and what these "artists" go through. So y'all really can only say so much for only what y'all see and hear. Demi is one of many addicts in this world and on this earth and instead of bashing her... because just as any other human being she is no different just because she has the money. Money doesn't mean shit if there's no support. And most of y'all "SHOULD" know money does not =happiness. If Demi was just a regular human without any fame and just like "us" working 9-5s every damn day but an addict on the regular or whatever that doesn't mean we should be judging her. She's STILL ONE OF US. FAME OR NO FAME. JUST LIKE MOST OF Y'ALL PROBABLY DOING DRUGS ON A REGULAR WHETHER ITS JUST WEED OR MORE.... CHILL WITH THE JUDGING BULL CRAP AND ACTUALLY SUPPORT HER. WE DON'T NEED MORE DAMN DEMONS ON THIS EARTH AND BELIEVE ME NO ONES PERFECT FOR ANYTHING. WE SHOULD BE HELPING EACH OTHER Y'ALL NOT THIS BULL SHIT THATS TEARING US APART EVERY DAY. SHIT WE JUST LOST KOBE BRYANT! THAT SHOULD BE A WAKE UP CALL RIGHT THERE!! AND DEMI COULD HAVE BEEN HIM TO BUT HELL THAT COULD HAVE BEEN ANY ONE OF US BUT ITS NOT. IF SHE WAS A REGULAR HOMELESS PERSON ON A CORNER SINGING/OR NOT SINGING FOR MONEY. YALL WOULDN'T HAVE IGNORED HER OR WOULD Y'ALL?? 🙄🙄🤔😔😔😔 smh.

snippet.textDisplay:
Beautiful </3
Everyone knows that 1 person that has been THRU SOME SH!
Surrounding that 1 person are top-toeing friends + fam, trying not to trigger that 1 person.
After what that 1 person has been thru, no one would BLAME them for remaining MESSED UP forever.
…but that 1 person doesn’t WANT to be messed up forever.
Epitomized by that 1 person screaming “is there anyone?!” Surrounded by others.
That, my friends, is how isolating life can be while recovering from trauma.
However, there is someone.
You are that someone.
You aren’t just anyone.
YOU are someone.
Anyone CAN BE that someone.

Reach out.
